Data Integration and Interoperability (DII) describes processes related to the movement and consolidation of data within and between data stores, applications and organizations. Integration consolidates data into consistent forms, either physical or virtual. Data interoperability is the ability for multiple systems to communicate Tools that support this capability are usually : ESB, ETL, API
